poem:
Underpass Echoes: A Jabberwocky-Style Verse
'Twas brillig, and the underpass did slither and skeeble;
Did gyre and gimble in the gloam with echoing roves.
All mimsy were the footfalls, and the lamps did gleam and gleed;
And the mome raths outgrabe the cadence the tunnel feeds.

Beware the echo-wraith, the clack-spiral in the rain;
It copies every whisper, and returns it twice again.
One-two, the tunnel mutters, with a chorus that won't fade;
Thus underpass and traveler trade in rhyme and shade.

Morning Fog, in Jabberwocky Style

'Twas mornish, and the fog did slither in the wabe;
The slithy mizzle-motes gyred and gimble, curling like a sail.
A pale borogove of sunshine peeped through the murk-veiled veil;
And hedgerows wore dew-ring garlands, glittering pale.
The world went hush, a muffled chorus of soft, shy sighs;
And boots and bikes woke slowly, blinking with tired eyes.
Fogsprogs drifted, twirlwhirred, in the trembly air;
They skimmed the meadows, leaving lace of gleam and glare.
The air smelled of rain-sugar and morning bread;
Morning wore a blanket of whispery gray-thread.
Then sun-bells pricked to life and loosened the gray's embrace;
And the Jabber-mirth of morning fog drifted away in grace.

The Burn-in Brillig

Brillig the screens, and slithy pixels glow;
All mimsy icons linger, muttering afterglow.
Beware the Ghostmark, a wraith within the pane;
It gnaws the borogoves of borders, leaving stain.

Frabjous flickers fizz and frindle through the night;
The afterimage yawps in pale, unceasing light.
O loblolly cursor, blink away the ache;
Yet burn-in lingers on, a patient, stubborn wake.

Mome-ward wander shade-wells, glimmer-scarred and sly;
Quiver-quaint remnant shapes refuse to die.
The glow grows long, and seals the frame in mire,
A ghostly banner tracing a long, lingering fire.

O frabjous day! The screen remembers still;
In idle moments, pale marks have their will.
